"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-bjztik hIbmEr pf-24_">What is standard 2 of the Care Certificate? </span></h2><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/What_is_standard_2_of_the_Care_Certificate_-_train_the_trainer_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.jpg?v=1692623999" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/What_is_standard_2_of_the_Care_Certificate_-_train_the_trainer_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.jpg?v=1692623999 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/What_is_standard_2_of_the_Care_Certificate_-_train_the_trainer_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK_500x.jpg?v=1692623999 320w" width="2000" height="1335" alt="What is standard 2 of the Care Certificate - train the trainer - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" title="What is standard 2 of the Care Certificate - train the trainer - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-leSONj uTJGF pf-25_"/><p class="sc-dMOJrz cGFGtP pf-26_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-bjztik hIbmEr pf-28_">The second standard of the Care Certificate revolves around the idea of continuous personal development. Teaching employees how to create and implement a Personal Development Plan (PDP) highlights the fact that learning should not be limited to just the initial induction training but should be a career-long pursuit. This culture of growth ensures that healthcare professionals are always updated, adaptable, and better equipped to tackle any emerging challenges. By providing training on Standard 2, employees can identify their unique strengths, weaknesses, and development areas. This individualised approach allows training efforts to focus on addressing specific skill gaps, resulting in more efficient and effective skill enhancement. </span></p><h3 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-jeraig eTNnJl pf-29_ _Y6RW61"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-bjztik hIbmEr pf-31_">Identify sources for learning and development </span></h3><img src